<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,933,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1582,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Remarks.</emphasis>
Was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[566,639,1583,1609]" name="Kenya" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Kenya</collectingCountry>
based on one female specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[1024,1227,1582,1608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,1618,1644]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
differ slightly in coloration from 
<typeStatus box="[634,732,1618,1644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[749,974,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Figs. 6–8 and 9–12</figureCitation>
). Since in most 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1935" box="[1159,1287,1618,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Macropsini">Macropsini</taxonomicName>
coloration is very variable, these differences cannot be the basis for describing Ethiopian specimens as a new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,933,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
Originally, was described in the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1978" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[779,1097,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,887,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Tsavopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori, R." box="[896,1097,1690,1716]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref7467" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1978) Studies on the family Cicadellidae (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha). 1. A revision of the Macropsinae of the Ethiopian Region. Acta Entomologica Fennica, 33, 1 - 17." type="journal article" year="1978">Linnavuori, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1836" box="[1281,1398,1691,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1398,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by very short crown and strongly developed median keel on pro- and mesonotum. However, in crown shape 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">M. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not differ from some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1836" box="[650,767,1763,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[650,767,1763,1788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[775,835,1763,1789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[851,1073,1761,1788]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–22" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1433,166,1785]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–22. 1–3—Macropsis simplex Jacobi, female (1—lateral view; 2—dorsal view; 3—face); 4–5—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n., male (4—lateral view; 5—dorsal view); 6–12—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori), female (6–8—holotype, photos by Alyssa Seemann; 9–12—females from Ambo, Ethiopia; 6, 9—face and pronotum; 7, 10–11—lateral view; 8, 12—dorsal view); 13–15—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n., female (13—lateral view; 14—dorsal view; 15—face); 16–22—Macropsis hippodameia Linnavuori (16, 19—male, lateral view; 17, 21—same, face; 18, 20—same, dorsal view; 22—female, lateral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Figs. 8, 12 and 2, 5</figureCitation>
). Also, in some species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[226,288,1799,1825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, median keel on the pro- and mesonotum is quite developed, although not to the same extent as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">M. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For this reason we share the opinion of 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton, K. G. A." box="[737,927,1834,1860]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" pagination="875 - 932" refId="ref7302" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (1980) Contributions to the study of the world Macropsini (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Canadian Entomologist, 112 (9), 875 - 932. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 112875 - 9" type="journal article" year="1980">Hamilton (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, who synonymizes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[1147,1255,1835,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1255,1835,1860]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Tsavopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macropsis)" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Macropsis">
<emphasis box="[1319,1436,1835,1860]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[161,278,1871,1896]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,933,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[199,366,1906,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[199,366,1906,1932]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">M. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="China" authorityYear="1925" box="[517,634,1907,1932]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri">
<emphasis box="[517,634,1907,1932]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">M. turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="China, W. E." box="[642,780,1905,1932]" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" pagination="361 - 374" refId="ref6984" refString="China, W. E. (1925) The Ethiopian species of Macropsis Lewis (Pediopsis auct.) (Homopt. Bythoscopidae). Eos, 1, 361 - 374." type="journal article" year="1925">
<collectingCountry box="[642,712,1906,1932]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">China</collectingCountry>
, 1925
</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[796,932,1905,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–81" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[258,1328,184,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[256,1332,166,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41–81. 41–43—Macropsis simplex Jacobi; 44–48—M. tincta Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 49—M. chinai Metcalf; 50—M. kanongensis Evans; 51—M. capensis (Cogan); 52–55—M. tuberculata (Linnavuori); 56–58—M. turneri China; 59–62—M. viridofulgida Tisheсhkin sp. n.; 63–67— M. hippodameia Linnavuori; 68–70—M. minuscula Linnavuori; 71–72—M. bussaensis Linnavuori; 73–76—M. thargelia Linnavuori; 77–79—M. nigrosignata (Stål); 80–81—M. bitaeniata Linnavuori. 41–42, 55, 59–60—2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 43, 61–62—female 7th sternite; 44—male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 45, 49–51, 63–64, 68, 71, 73, 77, 80—penis, lateral view; 46—pygofer process, lateral view; 47—pygofer processes, back view; 48, 67, 70, 76, 79, 81—style; 52, 57—head, pro-, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 53, 56—forewing; 54, 58—female genital segments, ventral view; 65–66, 69, 72, 74–75, 78—style tip. 49–50, 63–81—after Linnavuori (1978), 51—after Theron (1970), 56–58—after China (1925)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772393/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Figs. 56–58</figureCitation>
) in shape of head and pronotum, coloration, very short ovipositor and the presence of black tubercles on veins of forewing. For this reason we preliminary include it into the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="China" authorityYear="1925" box="[331,409,1979,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri">
<emphasis box="[331,409,1979,2004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Investigation of male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1978" box="[956,1121,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tsavopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[956,1121,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">M. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is necessary to ascertain the position of this peculiar species among Ethiopian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1836" box="[828,945,2015,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,945,2015,2040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="367">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772389" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3772389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3772389/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="368" startId="3.[151,264,1804,1829]" targetBox="[161,1422,173,1777]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1804,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="368">
